<p>Both are the same.The difference is how you use it.
Convention is,</p>

<p><strong>s</strong>tring is for variables </p>

<p><strong>S</strong>tring is for calling other String class methods</p>

<p>Like:</p>

<pre><code>string fName = "John";
string lName = "Smith";

string fullName = String.Concat(fName,lName);

if (String.IsNullOrEmpty(fName))
{
  Console.WriteLine("Enter first name");
}
</code></pre>
